This page stole my videos and their page and shop link has nothing to do with me. They’re immediately deleting my comments responding to people who want to purchase. 

When you can click on and buy a physical design, you will hear it from me first!! It’s especially hurtful to have my AR videos used to scam people while I am working hard on physical products. The trust between designer and audience is sacred and I don’t want my work associated with random shops and links that are not me. I am so happy that people are loving my designs and equally heartbroken that I can’t reply to them on this page with the correct info. 

It takes some time to create something physical that is truly as exciting as the digital pieces, and as one person I can’t compete with huge pages stealing my concept art out of my context to get web traffic. 

All of the correct info about what you’re seeing and augmented reality is all over my pages, but I can’t control it once a video is stolen and goes viral like this and others have💔💔 please wait for information straight from me about what is digital and what is physical from of my brain and designs, and report these if you see them⚙️.

Using the attention drawn to this video to say please consider humanitarian aid for the people of Palestine during this time, as well as expressing your views to those who represent you politically. Taking time to educate yourself now is WORTH IT and much more valuable than regular content. We have direct access to countless charities serving civilians in desperate need of medical attention and vital resources - and the world has turned its back long enough. This exact video reached 14.4M people the first time around so if your attention has been drawn, I urge you to educate yourself deeper about this crisis and how it has been presented to us through the media. Where US dollars are going and the devastating effects of Islamophobia on the public and representatives alike. Ask questions and seek answers, and once your views are clear - take action as you are able from places of privilege and safety for the sake of the people of Palestine and those who are facing oppression and atrocities worldwide as their reality. You do not have to be a politician, an academic, or anything in particular at all to come to a better understanding. Question where the differences in perception, compassion, urgency, and action lie in the masses and from our representatives. But actionably and tangibly, humanitarian aid to civilians in need should never be a contentious issue.

In my work recently I’ve been exploring the idea of two things existing in the same 3D space with some elements of visual proof, meaning as they turn, they don’t occlude but continue to appear to be taking up the same space in a way we would not be able to conceive of or solve visually before a 3D digital layer over our reality. I hope these explorations will introduce this concept into AR and influence the design of our 3D layer of the future. ✨

The biggest one who used my videos has 37M views on just one platform of three, all with completely wrong info💀 Hopefully 2024 is the year where everyone who has already seen these around can find me🩶 I have so many resources on this platform and others if you want to learn more about AR.

It is so damaging to my business and more as a smaller creator for a LARGE creator to show himself “ordering” a ring from me (???) after seeing my video and receiving a package from those videos. Implying that I try to scam people selling my clearly labeled augmented reality rings as physical objects. It would have taken someone on his team five minutes or less to find who actually made this and what it is no matter where he first saw my video- considering his other videos are him ordering and trying products where he has to make some kind of exchange with a seller. I receive threats, unwanted comments, and unwanted messages constantly from his audience months later for commenting that the videos of the rings are actually just my stolen art and I am an artist who clearly labels my work on my page. Now I have thousands of people who have no clue what’s going on calling me and my actual business a scam and thanking this creator for “exposing” what I “sell.” Portraying my art as a scam on this extreme scale has damaged so many people’s understanding of augmented reality and what I make. 

I’m posting this so I can pin it and hopefully people who come to my page can learn what augmented reality is. That’s the point of my entire page and presence. I want to make things no one has seen before. I never comment on any other page who has shared my work without permission and it happens DAILY. I don’t even care until it’s making these kind of claims that have confused millions of people on emerging tech and art. I have genuinely gotten sick of seeing the comments. Even on my birthday I couldn’t open the app without truly disgusting things being said to me from his audience.

Some people try to move art and creativity forwards, and cherish those things. Others wear abominably wack bowl cuts and bring social media so much further away from those sacred realms.

This is my Head on a Ring. It is fully real time capture augmented reality.

AR software now has a lot of integrated ways to use AI. I use image tracking to add 3D onto a tracker. My work hasn’t yet included any generated images, concepts, models, and it’s not edited using AI after the fact. A lot of times comments say AI when they mean to say AR 😁.
